<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 02 at 1:14AM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Texas
County through 145 AM CDT...
At 114 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles southeast of Hough, or 8 miles north of Guymon, moving
northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and dime size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Guymon, Hooker, Tyrone, Optima and Hough.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
